Andre de Ruyter has been appointed Eskom CEO. His appointment will take effect on 15 January 2020. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) is rejecting the appointment of Andre de Ruyter as Eskom CEO. De Ruyter will take over the reins at the embattled power utility in January. The party says this is a clear demonstration of a deliberate intent to collapse Eskom. READ: Mabuza: Eskom's assets not well-maintained The EFF is also accusing Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan of undermining Africans. The red berets say Gordhan and President Cyril Ramaphosa are reversing transformation at state-owned entities. The party's urging workers, trade unions and civil society to reject de Ruyter's appointment.